cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "ai-mutation: a citation-grounded, multi-modal retrieval-augmented pipeline for variant interpretation"
abstract: >
  ai-mutation turns a free-text mutation query into an evidence-grounded
  three-stage biomedical reasoning report. It performs parallel retrieval
  across nine public knowledge bases, optionally augments the prompt with
  a UniProt-derived domain map for vision-capable LLMs, and audits every
  LLM-emitted citation against the retrieved evidence with a
  deterministic citation-grounding verifier.
authors:
  - family-names: "<Author>"
    given-names: "<Given>"
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0000-0000-0000"
keywords:
  - variant interpretation
  - retrieval-augmented generation
  - large language models
  - hallucination mitigation
  - precision oncology
  - bioinformatics
license: MIT
